OL,3,CBudget 2025: Will Reeves scrap the
OL,4,Ccontroversial two-child benefit cap?
OL,6,FThe two-child benefit cap, which
OL,7,Fcurrently affects more than 1.5
OL,8,Fmillion children in the UK, could be
OL,9,Fscrapped as the Chancellor Rachel
OL,10,FReeves prepares to deliver her second
OL,11,Fbudget.
OL,13,FThe cap, which was introduced under
OL,14,Fthe last Conservative government,
OL,15,Fprevents most families from claiming
OL,16,Funiversal credit or child tax credit
OL,17,Ffor any third or additional children
OL,18,Fborn after April 2017.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/17
