OL,3,CBudget 2025: Will Reeves scrap the
OL,4,Ccontroversial two-child benefit cap?
OL,6,FReversing it would, in the long run,
OL,7,Fbring around 630,000 children out of
OL,8,Fabsolute poverty at a cost of roughly
OL,9,F#5,700 per child, according to the
OL,10,FInstitute for Fiscal Studies (IFS).
OL,12,FHowever, the IFS says, if the policy
OL,13,Fwere reversed, children in larger
OL,14,Ffamilies would still have
OL,15,Fsubstantially higher rates of poverty
OL,16,Fthan those in smaller families.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/17
